      "content": "but it didn't feel psychological. it felt technical. like there was a specific sub-audible pulse happening right when the crowd started cheering for the platform. i've heard people talk about how certain groups use infrasound or psychoacoustics to help drive mass emotion or compliance during events. do you think it's possible they're using those kinds of tools to make the crowd—and the viewers—more reactive to what they're saying?",
